Music Search API

This project is an API that allows you to search for music-related information. You can search for artists, get albums by artist ID, and retrieve tracks by album ID. It uses the Chinook database, an SQLite database containing music-related data.

How to Run the Project

1/ Clone the Git Repository

git clone <Git-repository-URL>

2/ Set Up the Python Environment

python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Linux/Mac
venv\Scripts\activate  # On Windows

3/ Install Dependencies

pip install -r requirements.txt

4/ Run the FastAPI API

uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000

5/ Run the Client (Optional)

python client.py

Using the API

The API has three main routes:

A. /artists/: Used to search for artists by name.
B. /albums/: To get albums by artist ID.
C. /tracks/: To get tracks by album ID.
